definition: woods/forest/CL:片[pian4]/circle(s) (i.e. specific group of people)/a collection (of similar things)
-ly/structural particle: used before a verb or adjective, linking it to preceding modifying adverbial adjunct

sentences.english: Every single one has a character of its own.
sentences.chinese: 每塊林地都有自己的特色。

sentences.english: It elaborates the factors influencing forestland value.
sentences.chinese: 闡述了影響林地價值的因素。

sentences.english: Deciding whether to use Hickory Woodlots or Forests is a debate outside the content of this article.
sentences.chinese: 使用山胡桃植林地或者是樹林不在本文討論之列。

sentences.english: The content of different form nitrogen in vegetable field is higher than wood soil.
sentences.chinese: 土壤中各種形態氮的含量菜地上壤高於林地土壤。

sentences.english: The anti-erosion indexes have close relations with soil capillary por…
sentences.chinese: 林地土壤抗衝性的強弱是其相關因子綜合作用的結果。

sentences.english: The new road was hacked out of the jungle.
sentences.chinese: 這條新路是在叢林地帶開闢出來的。

sentences.english: The woodlands have hushed their songs, and doors are all shut at every house.
sentences.chinese: 林地裏，歌聲歸於沉寂，家家戶戶都關門了。

sentences.english: The root distribution in soil profile has also large effect on activity of the soil enzymes.
sentences.chinese: 林木根系分佈規律對林地土壤酶活性有重要的影響。

sentences.english: Our earliest ancestors also typically occupied woodland environments.
sentences.chinese: 我們最早的祖先也通常生活在林地環境中。

sentences.english: Spring is working it's magic on the woodland floor, spreading a carpet of bluebells.
sentences.chinese: 春天在林地上施展魔法，灑滿一地的風鈴草。

sentences.english: The men of bivouac made the clean forest land into great confusion.
sentences.chinese: 野營者們把乾淨的林地搞得亂七八糟。

sentences.english: After the color in the woodlands, the leaves will blanket the soil.
sentences.chinese: 林地裏斑斕的葉片將爲大地鋪上一層厚毯。

sentences.english: He was forced to sign a contract selling his father's forestland .
sentences.chinese: 他被迫簽訂合同出售他父親的林地。

sentences.english: The Longsheng rice terraces are a popular destination for many visitors in Guangxi.
sentences.chinese: 龍勝梯田受到許多到桂林地區旅遊者歡迎的遊覽景點。

sentences.english: Adult langurs spend most of their day in the forest canopy feeding on leaves.
sentences.chinese: 大多數情況下成年葉猴都在林地的樹冠上採食樹葉。

sentences.english: The convoy of Chinese peacekeeping transportation detachment are traveling across the vast forest in west Africa.
sentences.chinese: 中國維和運輸分隊的車隊穿越西非茫茫叢林地帶。
